2 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 383 IS CREATED TO
3 READ AS FOLLOWS:
4 In an area that has adopted planning and zoning pursuant to KRS Chapter 100, a
5 property owner shall not lease or allow to be occupied any multi-family housing unit or
6 accessory dwelling unit located on a lot that contains a single-family home and which
7 is located in a traditional single-family home zone as defined in Section 1 of this Act,
8 unless the owner primarily resides in the single-family home on the lot.
